# Locale JSON — never remove `//ok` comments

In `client/src/i18n/locales/**/*.json`, translators mark reviewed strings with a trailing line comment: `//ok` (e.g. `"label": "…", //ok`).

**Never remove, strip, or drop these comments** when editing locale files.

## Safe editing

- Prefer text-aware tools that use `scripts/parse-locale-json.mjs` (`readLocaleJson`, `stripTrailingLineComment`, `extractTrailingComment`, `joinLocaleFileLines`).
- **Do not** round-trip locale files through `JSON.parse` + `JSON.stringify` (or `writeFileSync(JSON.stringify(...))`) — that erases all `//ok` and length comments.
- If you must remove obsolete keys, edit line-by-line or run `node scripts/restore-ok-comments.mjs` afterward (realigns `//ok` from git `HEAD` by line content and JSON path).
- `sync-locale-keys.mjs` only inserts missing keys and runs restore automatically; it does not rewrite whole files.

## `//ok` meaning

`//ok` means the translation is approved. Leave it on the line unless the string value itself changes and needs re-review (then update the text and keep or refresh the comment per team practice).
